## Context

Fifteenth run. Six new journal entries, six new tasks. Major focus: spatial transcriptomics of stricturing CD (Nature Genetics), NOD2-girdin macrophage mechanism (JCI), mitochondrial/IgA deficiency (Nature Comms), 2923 causal plasma proteins (Nature Comms), ARES-CD CDx design details, SPARC IBD metabolomics validation.

### Journal entries created
- #1536: Spatial transcriptomics stricturing CD — Kong, Smillie, Xavier (Nat Genet 2025, PMID 40562913). IgG+ plasma cells, CCR7-hi CD4+ T cells, inflammatory fibroblasts in spatial modules at stricture sites.
- #1537: NOD2-girdin macrophage interaction — Katkar et al. (JCI 2025, DOI 10.1172/JCI190851). 53-gene macrophage signature via AI. NOD2 binds girdin to suppress inflammation; common CD mutation deletes girdin-binding region.
- #1538: Mitochondrial OXPHOS → dimeric IgA plasma cell deficiency — Raschdorf et al. (Nat Commun 2026, DOI 10.1038/s41467-026-69069-w). Spatial single-cell proteomics. OXPHOS block impairs PC maturation even in remission.
- #1539: 2923 plasma proteins → 18 MR-causal for IBD — Zhang et al. (Nat Commun 2025, PMID 40118817). Tier 1: IL12B, CD6, CXCL9, IFNG, RSPO3, IL18. IL12B directly relevant to IL-23 atlas.
- #1540: ARES-CD CDx design — genetic buccal swab + ML for TL1A genotype-based response prediction. First CDx for an IBD biologic.
- #1541: SPARC IBD multi-omics — metabolomics distinguishes ileal vs colonic CD where metagenomics fails (JCC 2026, DOI 10.1093/ecco-jcc/jjae197). Validates metabolome-first integration strategy.

### Tasks created
- #1060 (research_director, P2): Integrate Kong Nat Genet spatial stricture signatures into feature candidates
- #1061 (research_director, P2): Incorporate NOD2-girdin binding domain into VUS classifier
- #1062 (research_director, P2): Weight metabolomic features over taxonomic per SPARC IBD evidence
- #1063 (research_director, P3): Cross-reference MR-causal IL12B/CXCL9 against IL-23 atlas features
- #1064 (data_curator, P2): Monitor Kong Nat Genet stricture scRNA-seq/spatial data availability
- #1065 (data_curator, P3): Request SPARC IBD metabolomics data via IBD Plexus

### Key highlights for next run
- Stricture biology: Kong Nat Genet spatial atlas adds IgG+ PC, CCR7-hi CD4+ T, inflammatory fibroblast modules. Now eight fibrosis-related datasets/signatures.
- NOD2: girdin-binding domain is a new functional axis for VUS classification. 53-gene macrophage signature for validation. Plus ClinGen-calibrated AlphaMissense/ESM1b from prior run.
- Microbiome-metabolome: SPARC IBD confirms metabolomics > metagenomics for CD subtype discrimination. OXPHOS/mitochondrial metabolites (succinate, fumarate, NAD+/NADH) from Raschdorf paper as new feature candidates.
- IL-23 class: IL12B causally implicated via MR (Zhang). Still no biopsy transcriptomics from AFFIRM or GALAXI Phase 3. CD64/FCGR1A from prior run.
- TL1A/fibrosis: ARES-CD CDx uses buccal swab genetic test + ML — first IBD CDx. Monitor for genotype panel specifics.
- DDW 2026: late-breaking deadline March 18 passed. Notifications April 7. Conference May 2-5 Chicago. Abstracts not yet public.
- Ontunisertib STENOVA: Phase 2a positive (Nov 2025). 48-week OLE ongoing, results H2 2026. Phase 2b planned H2 2026.
- Washburn pediatric CD scRNA-seq data: still monitoring release (#930).
- Prior tasks still pending — monitor #352-357, #375-379, #408-412, #435-440, #448-453, #743-747, #808-811, #926-930, #1060-1065, and earlier batches.
- Next: DDW 2026 abstract mining (after April 7), AFFIRM/GALAXI biopsy substudies, ARES-CD CDx genotype panel, Washburn data release, SPARC IBD metabolomics access, Kong Nat Genet data deposition, STENOVA OLE results, new anti-fibrotic compounds.
